30 3 Caesarem Sinuessae: he was there probably on the 27th and the next day at Formiae, where he had an interview with Cicero. Pompey had already left Italy, having sail‘ed from Brundisium. Caesar had followed him so far and was now returning to Rome by way of Capua. His interview with Cicero was for the purpose of deterring him from joining Pompey and of urging him to return to Rome.
